RISK_LOG_NOTE: Per Robert Christie in VTAM MFR Comments: Further clarification is needed for "One landowner cannot receive 25% of the benefits." Page 3-12 of ER 1105-2-100 states that a single private beneficiary cannot receive 100% of the benefits. Further investigation finds that the guidance for emergency levee repairs under PL 84-99 (Appendix D of EP 500-1-1). Note that even for the specific case of emergency levee repairs under PL 84-99, this guidance does *not* require that no landowner receive more than 25% of the benefits, only that PDTs must ?identify the magnitude of benefits received by any single beneficiary if these benefits exceed 25 percent of total benefits.?
